<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,445,760]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,445,471]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body small and moderately slender. Coloration brown, with various whitish, black and green spots on the extremities and the tegmina (
<figureCitation box="[515,660,481,507]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-21@42.[151,1436,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 24. Alexanderellus n. gen. species. A, C–E. A. mariposa n. comb. B., F–I. A. kumangui n. sp. (Photos: A and C. A. Gorochov. Figs. D and E. after Gorochov, 2012)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876273/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Figs. 24A, B</figureCitation>
). Head longer than wide and relatively narrow in profile; vertex moderately raised, ocellar tubercle little developed (
<figureCitation box="[687,831,517,543]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-21@42.[151,1436,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 24. Alexanderellus n. gen. species. A, C–E. A. mariposa n. comb. B., F–I. A. kumangui n. sp. (Photos: A and C. A. Gorochov. Figs. D and E. after Gorochov, 2012)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876273/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Figs. 24C, F</figureCitation>
); antennae filiform with a few dispersed nodes on the flagellum. Meso- and metazona of pronotal disc elevated progressively (
<figureCitation box="[979,1125,553,579]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-21@42.[151,1436,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 24. Alexanderellus n. gen. species. A, C–E. A. mariposa n. comb. B., F–I. A. kumangui n. sp. (Photos: A and C. A. Gorochov. Figs. D and E. after Gorochov, 2012)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876273/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Figs. 24C, F</figureCitation>
). Tegmina transparent with some diffuse spots; ventro-distal portion of anal margin gently expanded; hind femur with a distal foliose spine (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-21@42.[151,1436,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 24. Alexanderellus n. gen. species. A, C–E. A. mariposa n. comb. B., F–I. A. kumangui n. sp. (Photos: A and C. A. Gorochov. Figs. D and E. after Gorochov, 2012)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876273/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 24B</figureCitation>
). Cerci laterally flattened, with triangular branches of similar shape.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
